title: Billie Lourd Shares Peaceful Nature Photo After Deaths of Carrie Fisher and Debbie Reynolds
text: Billie Lourd Shares Peaceful Nature Photo After Deaths of Carrie Fisher and Debbie Reynolds by Jackie Willis 5:30 AM PST, February 07, 2017 Playing Billie Lourd Shares Peaceful Nature Photo After Deaths of Carrie Fisher and Debbie Reynolds Billie Lourd is getting back to nature as she continues to grieve. After the deaths of her mother, Carrie Fisher, and grandmother, Debbie Reynolds , in December, the 24-year-old actress shared a photo of herself looking at peace while standing next to a body of water. Lourd captioned the photo with the hashtags "#Blas√©OnTheOutsideBlessedOnTheInside," "#ByTheBayou" and "#FindingTheFunny." A photo posted by Billie Lourd (@praisethelourd) on Feb 6, 2017 at 3:18pm PST A photo posted by Taylor Lautner (@taylorlautner) on Feb 6, 2017 at 1:52pm PST Lourd commented: "Missin my baes." WATCH: Billie Lourd Jets Off to Cabo With Taylor Lautner After Heartbreaking Family Deaths Lourd's recent getaway comes just a few weeks after she shared a lighthearted photo of herself hanging out with friends, who were all wearing onesies. "This group of onesie clad supremely supportive humans (and many others #notpicturedbutinthepicture) are the kings and queens of my world," she captioned the photo, along with the hashtags "#gratefulfortheirgreatness" and "#friendsfindingthefunny." "Finding the funny" appears to be advice Lourd is taking from her late mother. A few weeks ago, she posted a childhood photo of herself and quoted the Star Wars actress , writing: "If my life weren't funny then it would just be true and that is unacceptable." Lourd added, "Finding the funny might take a while but I learned from the best and her voice will forever be in my head and in my heart."
